241
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:43,900
I don't know a lot of them.

242
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:45,420
I've only seen them once or twice.

243
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:46,500
They're all just trying

244
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,380
to get close to Mr. Wu

245
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:48,660
since he won an award.

246
00:09:49,020 --> 00:09:49,860
I thought about it.

247
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:50,860
I didn't want

248
00:09:50,860 --> 00:09:52,580
to socialize with those acquaintances

249
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:54,340
so I didn't go.

250
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,260
Jiang Shiyan.

251
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,620
Do you think the reason

252
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:05,780
I haven't mentioned

253
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:07,260
Song Jing much over the years

254
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:08,860
is that he caused me

255
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:10,380
a lot of emotional pain?

256
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:18,500
Actually, I...

257
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:20,460
It's because

258
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:23,620
I feel embarrassed

259
00:10:23,620 --> 00:10:24,900
that I don't bring him up.

260
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:30,020
Can you elaborate?

261
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:38,620
Regardless of everything,

262
00:10:38,620 --> 00:10:40,660
we were high school classmates

263
00:10:40,900 --> 00:10:43,020
and ended up at the same university.

264
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:45,060
Though we weren't in the same major,

265
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,180
we were in the same dept.

266
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:47,940
We took many elective courses together.

267
00:10:48,860 --> 00:10:50,260
So at first,

268
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:52,500
we went to class together

269
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,900
and went to the library for books.

270
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,460
He was proactive in contacting me.

271
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,860
So, it looked a bit

272
00:10:57,860 --> 00:10:59,500
like we were dating.

273
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:01,740
But later,

274
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:03,140
I realized something

275
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:03,980
was off.

276
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:05,580
For example,

277
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:07,140
he asked me to help him

278
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:09,380
with some volunteer work
in the department,

279
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:10,660
but he went to attend

280
00:11:10,660 --> 00:11:11,860
some student council events.

281
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:12,700
What?

282
00:11:13,020 --> 00:11:14,140
He asked me out for dinner

283
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,380
but suddenly canceled,

284
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:17,020
saying he was going

285
00:11:17,020 --> 00:11:18,660
to a senior's birthday party.

286
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,900
In short, whenever that senior

287
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:21,860
called him,

288
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:23,220
he'd show up right away.

289
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:25,020
For things like picking up packages,

290
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,380
returning books,

